---
id: org.dxos.plugin.bookmarks
name: BookmarksPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Manages a list of clipped web pages. Bookmarks are created primarily via the
Composer browser extension's "Add bookmark" page action: the extension captures
a snapshot of the current page (title, URL, og metadata, selection) and this
plugin materializes it as a `Bookmark` object in the active space, with a link
back to the original page. Bookmarks render with existing UI components (card
and article surfaces) and can later be enriched with an AI-generated summary
(best-effort, not load-bearing for creation).

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term   | URI                            |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| `type` | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat` | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test` | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |

## Types

```mdl
type Bookmark
  desc: |
    A saved web page. All optional fields are best-effort: a bookmark is
    created even when the page exposes no metadata.
  fields:
    title: string                # hints.ogTitle ?? source.title
    url: string                  # the bookmarked page URL
    favicon?: string             # source.favicon
    image?: string               # hints.ogImage
    excerpt?: string             # hints.ogDescription ?? first 280 chars of selection text
    summary?: string             # optional AI summary (future; not set at creation)
    createdAt: string            # ISO timestamp, from snapshot source.clippedAt
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Bookmark Schema

  req F-1.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: the Bookmark ECHO type is registered with the schema module

  req F-1.2:
    when: a Bookmark is rendered anywhere typed labels are used
    then: its label is the `title` field and its icon is the bookmark icon
```

```mdl
feat F-2: AddFromSnapshot Operation

  req F-2.1:
    when: the operation is invoked with { snapshot, target }
    then: |
      a Bookmark is created in the target database with best-effort fields:
        title     ← snapshot.hints.ogTitle ?? snapshot.source.title
        url       ← snapshot.source.url
        favicon   ← snapshot.source.favicon
        image     ← snapshot.hints.ogImage
        excerpt   ← snapshot.hints.ogDescription ?? first 280 chars of selection.text
        createdAt ← snapshot.source.clippedAt
      and the operation returns { id } of the created object.

  req F-2.2:
    when: the snapshot carries no hints and no selection
    then: the Bookmark is still created (title falls back to the tab title)
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Page Action Contribution

  req F-3.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: |
      a page action "Add bookmark" is contributed under the plugin-crx
      PageAction capability with:
        urlPatterns: all http(s) URLs
        extractor:   snapshot
        contexts:    popup, page
        operation:   AddFromSnapshot

  req F-3.2:
    when: the browser extension lists page actions
    then: the action appears in the extension popup on any http(s) page
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Surfaces

  req F-4.1:
    when: a Bookmark is the subject of an article surface
    then: |
      a panel renders the title, image (when present), excerpt, summary
      (when present), and a button that opens the source URL in a new tab

  req F-4.2:
    when: a Bookmark is the subject of a card surface
    then: a card renders the title, excerpt, and image (when present)
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Snapshot mapping prefers og hints
  given: a snapshot with ogTitle, ogDescription, ogImage, favicon, clippedAt
  when: Bookmark.fromSnapshot is applied
  then:
    - title === ogTitle
    - excerpt === ogDescription
    - image === ogImage
    - favicon === source.favicon
    - createdAt === source.clippedAt
```

```mdl
test T-2: Snapshot mapping falls back without hints
  given: a snapshot with no hints and a long text selection
  when: Bookmark.fromSnapshot is applied
  then:
    - title === source.title (the tab title)
    - excerpt is the first 280 characters of the selection text
    - image is unset
```

```mdl
test T-3: AddFromSnapshot persists a Bookmark
  given: an in-memory database
  when: AddFromSnapshot is invoked with { snapshot, target }
  then:
    - a Bookmark object exists in the database
    - the operation returns the object's id
```

